  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0dd9\u0db3\u0dcf\u0db8 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0da9\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0 \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Russian gas trade catches the US",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the latest data released by the International Energy Agency (IEA), for the first time the United States has supplied more liquefied natural gas (LNG) to Europe than Russia sends through pipelines.",
        "Russia ships about 150 billion cubic meters of gas to Europe through pipelines each year, and in 2021 Russia will meet more than a third of the European Union's (EU) gas demand, the IEA said.",
        "However, in response to Western sanctions amid the Russia-Ukraine conflict, Russia in June cut off natural gas shipments to Europe via Nord Stream, halting gas supplies to Finland, Poland, Bulgaria and other European countries.",
        "Russia also said it plans to cut gas supplies to Germany in mid-July due to annual maintenance.",
        "By providing military aid to Ukraine, the US has taken advantage of this opportunity to further fuel the war against Russia and increase its LNG supply to Russian suppliers, with Europe cutting off shipments to countries that do not comply with the new payment terms.",
        "IEA Executive Director Fathi Birol tweeted, \"Given Russia's recent natural gas flow to the EU, this is the first month in history that the EU imported more gas from the US via LNG than it received from Russia by pipeline.\" Namely."
      ],
